OL,4,CMore swearing but parents want children
OL,5,Cprotected
OL,6, People are increasingly likely to use
OL,7, strong swearing in their everyday life,
OL,8, says research from the British Board of
OL,9, Film Classification (BBFC).
OL,11,FThe body, which gives age ratings to
OL,12,Ffilms, says about a third of people in
OL,13,Fthe UK are more likely to use strong
OL,14,Fswear words than five years ago.
OL,16,FBut the research found parents did not
OL,17,Fwant age restrictions weakened for
OL,18,Fswearing in movies and DVDs.
OL,20,FParents wanted to protect children "for
OL,21,Fas long as possible" from swearing.
